summary.name: birdstrikes.csv
summary.dataset_description: A dataset containing information about bird strikes on aircrafts

properties.description: The name of the airport where the bird strike occurred
The make and model of the aircraft involved in the bird strike
The amount of damage caused by the bird strike
The date of the flight when the bird strike occurred
The airline operator of the aircraft involved in the bird strike
The state where the flight originated from
The phase of the flight when the bird strike occurred
The size of the wildlife involved in the bird strike
The species of the wildlife involved in the bird strike
The time of day when the bird strike occurred
The cost of other damages caused by the bird strike
The cost of repairing damages caused by the bird strike
The total cost of damages caused by the bird strike
The speed of the aircraft in knots when the bird strike occurred

goals.question: What is the distribution of bird strikes by airport?
goals.rationale: This can help identify airports with high bird strike incidents and inform decisions on bird control measures.

goals.question: Which aircraft make and model has the highest number of bird strikes?
goals.rationale: This can help identify aircraft models that are more prone to bird strikes and inform decisions on aircraft design and maintenance.

goals.question: What is the distribution of bird strikes by wildlife species?
goals.rationale: This can help identify wildlife species that are more likely to cause bird strikes and inform decisions on wildlife management.

goals.question: What is the relationship between the speed of the aircraft and the amount of damage caused by bird strikes?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of Speed_IAS_in_knots vs Effect_Amount_of_damage
goals.rationale: This can help identify if there is a correlation between the speed of the aircraft and the amount of damage caused by bird strikes.

goals.question: What is the distribution of bird strikes by phase of flight?
goals.rationale: This can help identify the phase of flight when bird strikes are more likely to occur and inform decisions on flight operations and procedures.

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Airport_Name'].value_counts().plot(kind='bar')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of bird strikes by airport?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Aircraft_Make_Model'].value_counts().plot(kind='bar')
    plt.title('Which aircraft make and model has the highest number of bird strikes?', wrap=True)
    plt.axhline(y=data['Aircraft_Make_Model'].value_counts().max(), color='r', linestyle='-',
                label='Max number of bird strikes: {:.2f}'.format(data['Aircraft_Make_Model'].value_counts().max()))
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Wildlife_Species'].value_counts().plot(kind='bar')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of bird strikes by wildlife species?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Effect_Amount_of_damage'] = pd.Categorical(data['Effect_Amount_of_damage'], categories=['None', 'Minor', 'Medium', 'Major', 'Destroyed'], ordered=True)
    chart = data.plot.scatter(x='Speed_IAS_in_knots', y='Effect_Amount_of_damage', alpha=0.5, figsize=(10, 7), color='blue')
    chart.axhline(y='Destroyed', color='red', linestyle='--', label='Destroyed')
    chart.legend()
    plt.title('What is the relationship between the speed of the aircraft and the amount of damage caused by bird strikes?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
